# organization-hierarchy

Multi-tier organization structure with the following hierarchy:

Platform
└─ Agency
   └─ Client
      └─ Campaign

Key Components:

1. Credit Flow Management (Importance Score: 95)
- Unidirectional credit movement from Platform → Agency → Client → Campaign
- Credit pool inheritance with allocation tracking
- Balance monitoring and threshold alerts at each level
- Atomic credit operations with audit logging

2. Role-Based Permissions (Importance Score: 90)
- Hierarchical permission inheritance system
- Role capabilities:
  - Platform Admin: Full system access
  - Agency Owner: Gift card management, client creation
  - Client Owner: Campaign management, budget control
  - Call Center: Redemption workflows
- Cross-organization access controls with audit trails

3. Client-Agency Relationships (Importance Score: 85)
- One-to-many agency-client mapping
- Shared resource pools between agencies and clients
- Custom pricing rules per relationship
- White-label configuration options

4. Resource Inheritance Rules (Importance Score: 80)
- Gift card pool access inheritance
- Template sharing with override capabilities 
- Brand access controls with agency restrictions
- Campaign asset inheritance model

5. Multi-Tenant Data Model (Importance Score: 75)
- Organization-specific data isolation
- Shared resource management
- Cross-organization reporting capabilities
- Tenant-specific configuration storage

Core Business Rules:
1. Credits only flow downward in hierarchy
2. Permissions inherit downward with override capability
3. Resources can be shared laterally between same-level entities
4. Organizations can have custom pricing and markup rules
5. Each level maintains independent audit trails

